    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5430" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κομάω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κόμη</span>): only part., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">wearing long hair;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κάρη κομόωντες Ἀχαιοί</span>, ‘long-haired
          Achaeans;’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἀβαντες ὄπιθεν κομόωντες</span>,
          i. e. shorn in front, <i><span class="en">Il. 2.542</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἐθείρῃσι</span>, ‘with long manes,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 8.42</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
